Chelsea striker, Tammy Abraham, could join Zinedine Zidane’s Real Madrid at the end of the season. According to Don Balon, Real Madrid’s president, Florentino Pérez, who has signed some of the most promising young talents in the world such as Vinicius, Kubo, Martin Odegaard and Rodrygo Goes in recent years, is interested in signing Abraham. The Spanish newspaper reports that the Perez has identified the 22-year-old as a transfer target if the Los Blancos fail with an offer for Tottenham Hotspur striker, Harry Kane. The report added that Perez is currently not satisfied with the performance of Real Madrid attackers, Karim Benzema, Gareth Bale and Eden Hazard. Real Madrid are currently on top of the La Liga table with 18 points from eight games. Abraham has been impressive for Frank Lampard’s men so far this season. He has scored nine goals from eleven matches in all competition for the Blues. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.